
[1]zone

   ZONE, n. [L., Gr.]

   1. A girdle.

   An embroiderd zone surrounds her waist.

   2. In geography, a division of the earth, with respect to the
   temperature of different latitudes. The zones are five; the torrid
   zone, extending from tropic to tropic 46 degrees, 56 degrees, or 23
   degrees 28' on each side of the equator; two temperate or variable
   zones, situated between the tropics and polar circles; and two frigid
   zones, situated between the polar circles and the poles.

   3. Circuit; circumference.

   Ciliary zone, in anatomy, the black impression of the ciliary processes
   on the vitreous humor of the eye.
